- [David] Well, how
would you put it Scott?

38:08.750 --> 38:10.375
- Dude.

38:11.458 --> 38:13.166
I'm just trying to fix this.

38:13.166 --> 38:15.041
Or at least try.

38:15.041 --> 38:16.959
I mean I was looking
that shit online, dude.

38:16.959 --> 38:19.041
Like I even looked
up shit about people

38:19.041 --> 38:21.083
that cops wasted just
because they were in

38:21.083 --> 38:24.458
the wrong place at the
wrong fucking time.

38:24.458 --> 38:26.792
If you look guilty,
you're guilty.

38:26.792 --> 38:28.291
- You looked shit up.

38:28.291 --> 38:30.041
That's like going online
when you're a little sick

38:30.041 --> 38:31.959
and some website tells you
that based on your symptoms

38:31.959 --> 38:33.125
you have cancer when all
you really have is the flu.

38:33.125 --> 38:35.458
- Carlo, do we have anymore pot?

38:35.458 --> 38:36.417
- [Carlo] My body just
crashed into the wall.

38:36.417 --> 38:38.041
- Can I please hit that?

38:38.041 --> 38:38.542
(honking)

38:38.542 --> 38:40.041
- [Carlo] Fuck.

38:40.041 --> 38:42.291
What the hell was that?

38:42.291 --> 38:42.625
- Chill, okay?

38:44.917 --> 38:46.417
- [Scott] Oh shit.

38:54.542 --> 38:56.041
(knocking)

38:56.041 --> 38:56.917
- Tyler.

38:57.250 --> 38:59.333
Tyler!

38:59.333 --> 39:00.208
Seriously?

39:05.125 --> 39:06.166
(knocking)

39:06.166 --> 39:07.792
I know you're here.

39:10.166 --> 39:11.542
(knocking)

39:15.208 --> 39:17.250
You're still mad at me?

39:18.583 --> 39:20.667
- I don't have time
for this right now.

39:20.667 --> 39:24.667
- What?

39:24.667 --> 39:25.709
- Hey, what do you
think you're doing?

39:25.709 --> 39:28.250
- [Audrey] Looking for
David, have you seen him?

39:28.250 --> 39:30.667
- [Tyler] Why do you
need to talk to him?

39:30.667 --> 39:33.166
- I need advice on
music for the party.

39:33.166 --> 39:33.875
David?

39:33.875 --> 39:36.333
- Hey, you can't see David.

39:38.083 --> 39:39.709
- Why not?

39:41.083 --> 39:41.959
- He's...

39:44.041 --> 39:46.750
He's in his room with
a chick from school.

39:46.750 --> 39:47.875
He'd just be
embarrassed if he knew

39:47.875 --> 39:50.041
anyone else was here right now.

39:50.041 --> 39:52.750
- That's adorable.

39:52.750 --> 39:54.125
- Yeah, whatever.

39:58.166 --> 40:01.208
- You sure I can't stay?

40:01.208 --> 40:03.000
- Yeah, you gotta go.

40:07.375 --> 40:08.291
- Don't come tomorrow
if you're still

40:08.291 --> 40:09.875
acting like an ass.

40:15.166 --> 40:18.000
- Yes, but one of us lives!

40:18.000 --> 40:19.083
- So we just go at each
other like hit men?

40:19.083 --> 40:21.375
- What the fuck are you
not getting about this?

40:21.375 --> 40:22.667
- This plan!

40:22.667 --> 40:24.250
And Tyler, this is stupid.

40:24.250 --> 40:25.166
It really is.

40:25.166 --> 40:27.083
- [Scott] This is
seriously the best thing

40:27.083 --> 40:28.583
that we can do right now.

40:28.583 --> 40:29.625
- [David] You have no clue
what you're talking about!

40:29.625 --> 40:30.834
- And you do!

40:30.834 --> 40:31.709
Suddenly, you're
the fucking expert

40:31.709 --> 40:34.417
on what to do when
you kill a child.

40:34.417 --> 40:36.166
- No, but apparently
you are now!

40:36.166 --> 40:37.750
- [Radio Announcer]
Important announcement.

40:37.750 --> 40:39.458
Vegas police say
a 12 year old boy

40:39.458 --> 40:41.667
who went missing last night
still hasn't returned home.

40:41.667 --> 40:45.250
Bradley Holt was reported
missing this morning.

40:45.250 --> 40:46.417
His parents are urging
anyone with information

40:46.417 --> 40:48.792
about his whereabouts to contact

40:48.792 --> 40:51.250
the Las Vegas Police
Department immediately.

40:51.250 --> 40:52.959
- Holy shit dude.

40:52.959 --> 40:54.125
Oh we're fucked.

40:54.125 --> 40:55.875
- Relax, relax, we knew
this shit was gonna happen.

40:55.875 --> 40:56.458
- But now it's real!

40:56.458 --> 40:58.667
Now it's fucking real!

40:58.667 --> 41:00.041
Hey I gotta go, I
gotta get out of here.

41:00.041 --> 41:01.333
- Hey, no one's going anywhere.

41:01.333 --> 41:02.375
- [David] Carlo, let's
just take a breather.

41:02.375 --> 41:03.583
- Hey you stay away from me!

41:03.583 --> 41:06.291
- [David] Carlo calm
down, hey Carlo!

41:06.291 --> 41:07.250
- I can't do this!

41:07.250 --> 41:08.542
- What the hell man?

41:08.542 --> 41:11.041
- I don't want to go to jail,
I don't want to die like this!

41:11.041 --> 41:13.000
I agree.

41:13.000 --> 41:14.208
Agree with him.

41:15.917 --> 41:17.083
It makes sense.

41:19.083 --> 41:19.959
Fuck.

41:24.625 --> 41:27.375
I can't believe I just did that.

41:28.375 --> 41:32.041
I can't believe this
is actually happening.

41:40.834 --> 41:40.875
I'm in.

41:49.083 --> 41:51.583
Fuck.

41:51.583 --> 41:55.041
- Would somebody turn that
fucking thing off already!

41:58.000 --> 41:59.625
- David.

42:04.166 --> 42:05.750
It's our only option.

42:14.208 --> 42:16.667
- You're really gonna
kill your own brother?

42:16.667 --> 42:20.667
- I'd kill myself before
I'd let that happen, okay?

42:25.625 --> 42:30.041
But, you gotta realize
no matter what happens,

42:30.041 --> 42:30.667
our lives are over.

42:42.875 --> 42:43.709
- I'm spent.

42:50.375 --> 42:53.125
- What does that mean?

42:53.125 --> 42:53.667
- It means fine.

42:56.375 --> 42:58.625
Maybe you guys are right.

42:59.750 --> 43:02.291
Maybe I'm just in over my head.

43:41.208 --> 43:43.750
- [Tyler] This will
probably be good.

43:43.750 --> 43:45.500
Carlo, grab that, yeah.

43:45.500 --> 43:47.333
Bring it around here.

43:47.333 --> 43:49.333
- [Carlo] Sorry.

43:49.333 --> 43:51.542
That should be ready to go.

43:56.583 --> 43:58.291
- We killed Bradley.

43:59.333 --> 44:03.250
And now, I mean, as
you're watching this tape,

44:03.250 --> 44:04.792
by now we've killed ourselves.

44:08.166 --> 44:09.792
- Yeah, you make a
mistake like this

44:09.792 --> 44:12.250
and it changes the
rest of your life.

44:12.250 --> 44:13.875
- Dude.

44:14.792 --> 44:15.709
What life?

44:16.166 --> 44:18.041
Shit's over.

44:19.291 --> 44:20.792
- I had never even
met him before.

44:20.792 --> 44:21.417
- I knew him.

44:21.417 --> 44:22.875
We were neighbors.

44:22.875 --> 44:24.917
I mostly remember him just
running around his pool

44:24.917 --> 44:27.542
trying to get away
from his little sister.

44:27.542 --> 44:28.834
- No.

44:28.834 --> 44:31.375
He put us in this situation
by just showing up.

44:31.375 --> 44:32.125
- Not on purpose though.

44:32.125 --> 44:34.834
- It makes me so fucking mad.

44:34.834 --> 44:37.208
Honestly, I'd kill him
again if I had the chance.

44:37.208 --> 44:38.959
- Dude.

44:38.959 --> 44:40.125
- I'm just saying.

44:40.125 --> 44:43.417
- We didn't even know
he was coming over.

44:43.417 --> 44:45.333
Who's gonna believe that, right?

44:45.333 --> 44:47.500
- Yeah.

44:47.500 --> 44:50.583
- I want his parents
to know what happened.

44:50.583 --> 44:52.291
I want them to know
that we didn't mean it.

44:52.291 --> 44:53.917
- Of course we didn't mean it.

44:53.917 --> 44:55.458
But people are gonna
believe what they want

44:55.458 --> 44:57.417
which is why we're
forced to do this.

44:57.417 --> 44:57.834
- David though.

45:00.625 --> 45:03.041
That little shit is
so fucking lucky.

45:03.041 --> 45:05.583
He goes to his room
to make music right?

45:05.583 --> 45:07.000
To mix music?

45:07.000 --> 45:08.166
He didn't even hear
the gunshots go off

45:08.166 --> 45:13.083
because the music in his
phones is so fucking loud.

45:13.083 --> 45:14.125
And we didn't even tell
until the next day.

45:14.125 --> 45:16.959
- Tyler didn't have
anything to do with it.

45:16.959 --> 45:18.834
He said we were acting
like a bunch of tools

45:18.834 --> 45:21.333
and went off to
get some more beer.

45:21.333 --> 45:22.500
- And Carlo was with
us at the arcade

45:22.500 --> 45:26.625
but he left to go home
before we ever shot the guns.

45:26.625 --> 45:28.333
He had homework or something.

45:28.333 --> 45:31.667
- And even though Scott was
with us earlier that night,

45:31.667 --> 45:33.792
he wasn't there when
it actually happened.

45:33.792 --> 45:38.291
He got too drunk
and had to bounce.

45:38.291 --> 45:39.375
It was just the three of us.

45:39.375 --> 45:40.792
- But David wasn't there.

45:40.792 --> 45:41.542
- Tyler wasn't even there.

45:41.542 --> 45:43.667
- Carlo was never there.

45:43.667 --> 45:45.500
- Scott wasn't there.

45:47.041 --> 45:48.166
Drives are good?

45:48.166 --> 45:49.041
- Yeah.

45:52.166 --> 45:53.917
Now what?

45:53.917 --> 45:55.208
- We stash 'em.

45:55.208 --> 45:56.083
- Where?

45:58.083 --> 45:59.417
- Baby Jesus.

45:59.417 --> 46:01.166
In his basket.

46:01.166 --> 46:01.959
- [Tyler] What?

46:01.959 --> 46:02.542
- [David] No way.

46:02.542 --> 46:04.959
That's blasphemous.

46:04.959 --> 46:06.250
Put him under the camel.

46:06.250 --> 46:08.083
- Dude, what we did.

46:08.083 --> 46:08.959
That shit's blasphemous.

46:08.959 --> 46:10.125
- You're such an asshole.

46:10.125 --> 46:10.917
- I'm just saying.

46:10.917 --> 46:12.208
- Guys, shut up.

46:14.542 --> 46:16.041
It's going under the basket.

46:16.041 --> 46:17.417
It's a good idea.

46:19.667 --> 46:22.166
- You're right though.

46:22.166 --> 46:24.208
About what we did.

46:24.208 --> 46:26.208
It is blasphemous.

46:26.208 --> 46:28.166
Unforgivable, even.

46:28.166 --> 46:31.458
Even if our plan does work,
there's no escaping that.

46:31.458 --> 46:32.333
Ever.

46:33.792 --> 46:34.875
- Yeah, maybe.

46:36.291 --> 46:37.000
- Let's go.

46:37.000 --> 46:39.500
(haunting choral music)

46:39.500 --> 46:42.417
- Can I get a ride home?

47:06.208 --> 47:09.333
- I think it was a mistake
to cover him up like that.

47:09.333 --> 47:10.458
- What?

47:10.458 --> 47:11.625
- Bradley.

47:11.625 --> 47:15.458
It just seems wrong to
suffocate him under that tarp.

47:15.458 --> 47:17.750
- Suffocate him.

47:21.709 --> 47:23.875
I'm going to bed.

47:23.875 --> 47:27.208
(haunting choral music)

47:56.667 --> 47:58.291
- I couldn't sleep.

47:59.667 --> 48:02.333
- [Tyler] I feel like
my head's gonna explode.

48:02.333 --> 48:03.083
- Hungover?

48:15.125 --> 48:16.709
- Is that your gun?

48:17.917 --> 48:19.083
- Yeah.

48:19.083 --> 48:20.709
You might as well
take it though.

48:20.709 --> 48:23.208
Two's better than one, right?

48:24.542 --> 48:27.000
- I'm not taking it.

48:28.458 --> 48:30.583
- I'm not shooting anyone.

48:31.875 --> 48:33.041
Not my brother.

48:34.709 --> 48:36.417
Not my best friends.

48:37.500 --> 48:39.125
Besides...

48:40.834 --> 48:42.709
I'm pretty sure the odds
of us living are better

48:42.709 --> 48:45.208
if we don't gun each other down.

48:46.792 --> 48:47.667
- Right.

48:54.583 --> 48:55.875
We killed him.

48:59.917 --> 49:02.458
We actually fucking killed him.

49:04.417 --> 49:07.375
(crying)

49:21.250 --> 49:23.709
- Let's just call Scott
and Carlo and tell them

49:23.709 --> 49:27.959
that we're calling this off
and turning ourselves in.

49:30.959 --> 49:34.041
- What were we
thinking last night?

49:39.458 --> 49:41.125
Okay, I'll call them right now.

49:57.750 --> 50:00.792
- Is everything all right?

50:00.792 --> 50:01.250
- I don't know.

50:08.000 --> 50:11.458
You wanna go get some breakfast?

50:11.458 --> 50:12.875
- [Carlo] Yeah.

50:12.875 --> 50:13.750
- Yes!

50:17.250 --> 50:19.959
Wanna run inside first
and change or something?

50:19.959 --> 50:22.250
I'll wait in the car.

50:22.250 --> 50:24.041
- And listen to that
stupid bitch lecture me

50:24.041 --> 50:26.458
about not coming
home last night?

50:26.458 --> 50:27.333
Fuck no.

50:30.041 --> 50:31.709
- Is that Gail?

50:31.709 --> 50:32.125
- It's Pam now.

50:37.834 --> 50:38.834
Let's go eat.

50:38.834 --> 50:39.208
- [Carlo] Okay.

50:44.834 --> 50:47.375
- [Scott] Just get what
you want man, I got it.

50:47.375 --> 50:47.792
- You serious?

50:47.792 --> 50:49.709
- Totally.

50:49.709 --> 50:51.333
- [Waitress] What can
I get for you boys?

50:51.333 --> 50:51.375
- Um.

50:53.083 --> 50:55.834
I'll have the pancake egg thing.

50:56.709 --> 50:58.709
The coke.

50:58.709 --> 50:59.667
- Okay.

50:59.667 --> 51:01.291
- And does that come
with hash browns?

51:01.291 --> 51:03.583
- [Waitress] No, that's extra.

51:03.583 --> 51:05.208
- Is that cool?

51:05.208 --> 51:07.583
- Yeah man, get what you want.

51:07.583 --> 51:08.041
- Okay, yeah.

51:08.041 --> 51:08.583
Hash browns.

51:08.583 --> 51:10.709
- Okay.

51:10.709 --> 51:12.583
- And I'll take the
egg white omelette

51:12.583 --> 51:14.834
with spinach and mushrooms.

51:20.166 --> 51:20.917
Thanks.

51:20.917 --> 51:22.041
- All right.

51:25.417 --> 51:27.583
- [Scott] It's Tyler again.

51:27.583 --> 51:29.792
- Did he leave a voicemail?

51:29.792 --> 51:31.041
- No, a text.

51:33.250 --> 51:34.333
He said we all need to meet up.

51:34.333 --> 51:37.083
I just don't understand
why he's not texting you.

51:37.083 --> 51:39.667
- Well, I have no battery, so.

51:40.625 --> 51:41.542
- I don't know Carlo, dude.

51:41.542 --> 51:42.959
That's pretty fucking sketchy.

51:42.959 --> 51:45.083
Like why would he
need to see us?

51:45.083 --> 51:47.417
- Maybe he changed the plan.

51:51.041 --> 51:51.917
- Maybe.

51:55.583 --> 51:57.208
Carlo.

51:59.750 --> 52:02.917
Man, I just might
be paranoid but...

52:02.917 --> 52:04.208
Last night we all
agreed that this is

52:04.208 --> 52:05.542
the only way out, right?

52:05.542 --> 52:07.291
- Yeah.

52:07.291 --> 52:08.417
- Okay, well.

52:08.417 --> 52:09.333
Tyler wouldn't just
change his mind.

52:09.333 --> 52:12.208
Okay, he's too
fucking controlling.

52:12.208 --> 52:12.417
- Okay, so...

52:14.458 --> 52:14.500
What?

52:21.834 --> 52:24.041
- It's a trick.

52:25.542 --> 52:29.125
We go and see him, thinking
he's changed his mind,

52:29.125 --> 52:29.417
but he hasn't.

52:31.542 --> 52:36.458
He just wants to get us
when we least expect it.

52:36.458 --> 52:39.875
- Oh shit.

52:39.875 --> 52:40.750
Oh shit.

52:42.959 --> 52:45.041
Yeah, I think you're right.

52:45.041 --> 52:46.667
- I know I'm right.

52:49.375 --> 52:51.375
Holy shit bro,
he's gonna kill us.

52:55.959 --> 52:58.291
- He's not answering.

52:58.291 --> 52:58.750
- [David] And Carlo's is off?

52:58.750 --> 53:00.792
- Yeah.

53:00.792 --> 53:02.291
- Well, we have no choice then.

53:02.291 --> 53:05.917
We have to find them and tell
them that this thing is off.

53:11.166 --> 53:12.458
I don't want it.

53:14.709 --> 53:15.875
- Fine, but I'm keeping
mine on me until

53:15.875 --> 53:18.208
this is all cleared up.

53:18.208 --> 53:19.166
- Fine.

53:19.166 --> 53:20.834
And what about the confessions?

53:20.834 --> 53:22.083
We should get rid
of them, right?

53:22.083 --> 53:23.000
- Don't worry about
that right now,

53:23.000 --> 53:26.834
we need to find Scott
and Carlo first.

53:26.834 --> 53:27.959
- All right.

53:32.959 --> 53:37.125
- I'm sure they're just
at Scott's or something.

53:37.125 --> 53:38.000
- Okay.

